raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '2.0.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-shinyalert
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/shinyalert_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/shinyalert/shinyalert_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a7f2441282bcd6cde5e14d84212a2b4db27774af7e2edc1062cbce6d9615692c

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  noarch: generic
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-shiny >=1.0.4
    - r-uuid
    - pandoc
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-shiny >=1.0.4
    - r-uuid
    - pandoc

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('shinyalert')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('shinyalert')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://cran.r-project.org/package=shinyalert
  dev_url: https://github.com/daattali/shinyalert
  doc_url: https://daattali.com/shiny/shinyalert-demo/
  license: MIT
  summary: Easily create pretty popup messages (modals) in 'Shiny'. A modal can contain text,
    images, OK/Cancel buttons, an input to get a response from the user, and many more
    customizable options.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
